Peru’s Vilcanota mountain range provides water for millions of people and forms a key part of the Amazon’s complex water cycle. With support from Rolex and the National Geographic Society, climate scientists and Explorers Baker Perry and Tom Matthews have installed a state-of-the-art weather station on the summit of one of its highest mountains to monitor how this system is responding to growing threats of climate change and deforestation.
